OL,3,CJames Bulger's mother: I needed to see
OL,4,Cthe faces of my son's killers
OL,6,FIt remains an unusual decision ` and
OL,7,Fone that raises questions: What
OL,8,Fpurpose does identification actually
OL,9,Fserve? Who benefits from knowing the
OL,10,Fnames of these two deeply disturbed
OL,11,Fkids? The public may want to know `
OL,12,Fbut do we need to know?
OL,14,FDenise is in no doubt. She believes
OL,15,Fit's essential for us to understand
OL,16,Fexactly who the killers are and what
OL,17,Fthey have done. Anything less, she
OL,18,Fbelieves, tells only half the story.
OL,19,FWe must have full knowledge to
OL,20,Funderstand the crime.
