OL,3,CJames Bulger's mother: I needed to see
OL,4,Cthe faces of my son's killers
OL,6,FDenise says she needed to see the
OL,7,Ffaces of the boys who killed her
OL,8,FJames, the faces he saw in the final
OL,9,Fmoments of his life.
OL,11,FThat knowledge ` however painful -
OL,12,Fbrought her some degree of comfort.
OL,14,FShe describes bereavement as a long
OL,15,Froad; which she and her family are
OL,16,Fstill travelling.
